                            <comment id="12556109" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2008 23:05:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why the bigger input for the text area?  Anything really big would just be cut-n-pasted, no?&lt;br/&gt;
And the visible area doesn&apos;t affect how much text you can actually add (because of scrollbars), right?&lt;br/&gt;
I agree with using POST to work around URL size limitations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12556114" author="gsingers" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2008 23:26:24 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why the bigger input for the text area? Anything really big would just be cut-n-pasted, no?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s just easier to read once it is in there, instead of scrolling through lots and lots of lines or having to switch back and forth between browser and a text editor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actually, I think it would be nicer if it were taller and wider.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, I am fine w/ leaving the size as long as the POST gets fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
